   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>31.12.1881 Samstag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49096">Paris</placeName> December 31. 1881</p>
            <p>
               <persName key="176">Papa</persName> and I went to <orgName key="66864">the
                  Châtelet</orgName> in the evening to see the &#x201e;<name type="work" key="28505">Mille
                  et une nuits</name>&#x201c;<note type="reg">
                  <persName key="76882">Artus</persName>
               </note>
               which was very pretty; at the end of the 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> act there were a lot
               of women, dresses in silver cloth, which looked like a mass of diamants in the light
               hung up in the air going about as if they were swimming right up at the top of the
               stage for we were supposed to be under water; this is how it is managed: the woman is
               hung to the bottom of a cart which goes about on rails above the curtain and as the
               thread by which she is tied up is invisible it looks as if she was swimming or
               flying. The whole of the piece was very pretty. The smile of <persName key="5940">Cleopatra</persName>. and the infernal hunt after Aladins lamp were specially
               well got up. I came home in 1882. </p>
         </div>
